1
00:00:01,750 --> 00:00:07,650
The bride collapsed during her ceremony,
blood dribbling from her mouth.

2
00:00:07,650 --> 00:00:11,020
Doesn't your wife's champagne look odd?

3
00:00:11,020 --> 00:00:12,060
She was poisoned?

4
00:00:12,060 --> 00:00:14,230
Could you please assist me, Sakuraba?

5
00:00:14,230 --> 00:00:18,110
I won't forgive whoever harmed my wife.

6
00:00:18,110 --> 00:00:22,980
All attendees of the wedding are suspects.

7
00:00:26,350 --> 00:00:29,400
Truth be told, I actually have one lead.

8
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:31,080
A lead?

9
00:00:31,080 --> 00:00:33,260
The day before our ceremony...

10
00:00:34,150 --> 00:00:36,670
this letter was left in our mailbox.

11
00:00:44,370 --> 00:00:45,790
[Unhappiest wishes to you, Red Riding Hood]

12
00:00:47,960 --> 00:00:49,900
[Red Riding Hood]

13
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:53,540
An anonymous threat?

14
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:20,610
I see you two are getting along.

15
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:22,750
Sorry.

16
00:01:23,730 --> 00:01:25,730
Who is this "Red Riding Hood"?

17
00:01:25,730 --> 00:01:29,780
I have no idea.

18
00:01:31,090 --> 00:01:33,750
What is this a picture of?

19
00:01:33,750 --> 00:01:38,140
Not sure, but that's a person on the left.

20
00:01:38,140 --> 00:01:40,920
Did you ask Sayaka about these?

21
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:45,430
Yeah. She was just as lost as I was.

22
00:01:45,430 --> 00:01:47,620
If anything, she was terrified.

23
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:52,860
You suspect one of your wedding guests

24
00:01:52,860 --> 00:01:56,830
sent this letter, correct?

25
00:01:59,190 --> 00:02:01,770
First, there are both your parents.

26
00:02:02,330 --> 00:02:07,460
Then there are the bride's friends
from high school, Chie and Airi.

27
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:12,610
Finally, there are your guests.
Your friends from university, Sugiura -

28
00:02:12,610 --> 00:02:14,140
I won't believe it.

29
00:02:14,140 --> 00:02:15,150
What?

30
00:02:15,150 --> 00:02:17,640
They're all good people, alright?

31
00:02:18,420 --> 00:02:22,090
There's no way one of them is the culprit.

32
00:02:22,090 --> 00:02:23,380
Then we're done here?

33
00:02:23,380 --> 00:02:25,710
No, no.

34
00:02:27,070 --> 00:02:28,870
I'll push through.

35
00:02:29,510 --> 00:02:31,520
For Sayaka's sake.

36
00:02:32,970 --> 00:02:35,460
I will find the culprit.

37
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:42,740
How did you first meet Sayaka?

38
00:02:43,610 --> 00:02:48,020
This guy, Makoto,
introduced us a year ago.

39
00:02:48,020 --> 00:02:54,010
He said she was a friend of a friend.

40
00:02:55,090 --> 00:02:57,920
She was a shy girl.

41
00:02:57,920 --> 00:03:00,620
But she was equally as kind.

42
00:03:00,620 --> 00:03:03,210
I went on several dates with her.

43
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:09,660
But last autumn,

44
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:13,480
I noticed she wasn't acting like herself.

45
00:03:14,190 --> 00:03:17,780
She took leave from her work at a patisserie,

46
00:03:18,720 --> 00:03:21,340
and began seeing a therapist.

47
00:03:22,610 --> 00:03:24,030
Why?

48
00:03:24,030 --> 00:03:26,260
She was being harassed online.

49
00:03:27,090 --> 00:03:31,140
Negative reviews directed at her
were being posted on foodie sites.

50
00:03:31,850 --> 00:03:33,100
[Female, 20's, had terrible customer service]

51
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:35,830
"Terrible customer service".

52
00:03:35,830 --> 00:03:38,650
They were being posted everywhere.

53
00:03:38,650 --> 00:03:43,370
Eventually, the owner of that patisserie
pressured her to quit.

54
00:03:43,370 --> 00:03:45,450
If you continue to take days off...

55
00:03:45,450 --> 00:03:47,910
<i>That man offered her no support.</i>

56
00:03:47,910 --> 00:03:52,930
<i>He only backed her into a corner.</i>

57
00:03:52,930 --> 00:03:55,020
<i>I couldn't believe what I was hearing.</i>

58
00:03:55,020 --> 00:03:59,540
Wait, you were there when it happened?

59
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:01,050
Yeah.

60
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,630
I sat at a table a little distance away,

61
00:04:04,630 --> 00:04:09,800
<i>since we weren't officially a couple yet.</i>

62
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:16,200
<i>After the owner left, Sayaka cried.</i>

63
00:04:28,130 --> 00:04:30,360
<i>That's when I knew.</i>

64
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:34,440
I was going to protect her.

65
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:37,260
I wanted to protect her.

66
00:04:37,810 --> 00:04:41,040
Which eventually led to marriage.

67
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:45,840
I knew she was the only one for me.

68
00:04:46,370 --> 00:04:49,460
Sayaka was eager to marry as well.

69
00:04:49,460 --> 00:04:53,650
You're a kind man, Hayashida.

70
00:04:55,510 --> 00:04:57,150
Well...

71
00:04:58,140 --> 00:05:02,090
Men are duty bound
to protect the women they love.

72
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:11,240
<i>A certain principle
fuels his passion for her.</i>

73
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:14,580
<i>Would people call him an honorable man? Or...</i>

74
00:05:22,530 --> 00:05:24,100
Evening, Sakuraba.

75
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:26,000
Hope I'm not interrupting.

76
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:26,960
Good evening.

77
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:29,550
Here's my offering for today.

78
00:05:29,550 --> 00:05:30,870
Thank you.

79
00:05:30,870 --> 00:05:32,020
Where's Sachiko?

80
00:05:32,020 --> 00:05:33,370
She's over there.

81
00:05:33,370 --> 00:05:35,840
You had a friend over? Hello there.

82
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:38,340
Sachiko? Where are you, dear?

83
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:47,030
Is that your... girlfriend?

84
00:05:47,030 --> 00:05:48,330
What?

85
00:05:48,330 --> 00:05:51,700
I mean, she barged in with a spare key.

86
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:54,150
That's Mrs. Yonemura.

87
00:05:54,150 --> 00:05:58,940
She's a fellow cat lover
who comes to care for Sachiko.

88
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:03,070
Your cat's name is "Sachiko"?

89
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:04,220
Yes?

90
00:06:04,220 --> 00:06:05,420
Odd name.

91
00:06:05,420 --> 00:06:08,430
You think? Sachiko is a girl's name.

92
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:11,620
What's so odd about it?

93
00:06:12,910 --> 00:06:14,730
Right, before I forget.

94
00:06:14,730 --> 00:06:16,220
I wanted to ask.

95
00:06:17,010 --> 00:06:21,050
How do you read this first name of yours?

96
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:27,240
It's read, "Sapphire".

97
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:34,950
My name is Sapphire Sakuraba.

98
00:06:35,790 --> 00:06:39,050
S-Sapphire?

99
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:49,790
Oh my, isn't that Kaori's daughter?

100
00:06:49,790 --> 00:06:51,950
You know Sayaka?

101
00:06:51,950 --> 00:06:54,930
Right, Sayaka! What a familiar face.

102
00:06:54,930 --> 00:06:58,140
Our families used to be neighbors.

103
00:06:58,140 --> 00:07:03,560
Wow, she's become an absolute beauty.

104
00:07:05,210 --> 00:07:06,440
And you're her husband?

105
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:07,720
Yes, I am.

106
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:11,250
Gosh, what a small world!

107
00:07:11,250 --> 00:07:13,570
Isn't that right, Sachiko?

108
00:07:13,570 --> 00:07:17,750
I remember Sayaka and her violin.

109
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:19,950
Kaori always boasted about her playing.

110
00:07:19,950 --> 00:07:22,260
If only she didn't get hurt...

111
00:07:22,260 --> 00:07:23,670
Hurt?

112
00:07:23,670 --> 00:07:29,620
She fractured her left arm
in elementary school.

113
00:07:29,620 --> 00:07:35,800
Yes. She could no longer pursue
a professional career in violin.

114
00:07:38,590 --> 00:07:42,790
What happened afterwards
was especially a pity.

115
00:07:42,790 --> 00:07:44,540
Pardon?

116
00:07:44,540 --> 00:07:49,090
Oh, look at me blabbering again.

117
00:07:49,090 --> 00:07:52,880
Gosh, it's already 7.
I have to get home and feed my own kitties.

118
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:54,850
I'll visit again.

119
00:08:00,950 --> 00:08:02,390
Say...

120
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,690
Aren't you...

121
00:08:07,690 --> 00:08:10,070
Getting hungry? Yes.

122
00:08:10,730 --> 00:08:12,430
How about you, Sachiko?

123
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:27,960
That was delicious.

124
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:29,840
Thanks for the food.

125
00:08:30,570 --> 00:08:32,540
Hayashida.

126
00:08:32,540 --> 00:08:35,190
There's something I want to confirm with you.

127
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:42,840
Does the champagne here look normal to you?

128
00:08:43,910 --> 00:08:45,070
Yeah.

129
00:08:45,070 --> 00:08:48,420
In other words, this is the "before".

130
00:08:48,420 --> 00:08:51,520
And this, is the "after".

131
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:53,260
It's gotten darker.

132
00:08:53,260 --> 00:08:54,660
That's right.

133
00:08:55,330 --> 00:08:57,160
Come here.

134
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,910
The before was taken at 3:45PM.

135
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:03,220
[3:45PM]

136
00:09:03,950 --> 00:09:08,440
The after, at 3:50PM.
Only five minutes later.

137
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:14,090
I see. Someone poisoned her in that time.

138
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,720
Thank you.

139
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:24,610
<i>I have no picture of Sayaka's glass
in this five minute window.</i>

140
00:09:24,610 --> 00:09:31,120
But I can identify the individuals
who had access to her drink.

141
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:36,400
First, sitting to her left
was the groom, Hayashida.

142
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:40,310
You could have easily poisoned her drink.

143
00:09:40,310 --> 00:09:42,210
Hey.

144
00:09:43,260 --> 00:09:45,280
Why would I do that?

145
00:09:46,290 --> 00:09:50,830
Next, sitting to her right
was the bride's mother, Kaori.

146
00:09:50,830 --> 00:09:53,300
Her mother is also innocent.

147
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:54,220
You think so?

148
00:09:54,220 --> 00:09:57,000
Sayaka is her daughter.

149
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,020
She wouldn't poison her own child.

150
00:09:59,870 --> 00:10:00,840
Then that leaves two suspects.

151
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:02,530
Mr. Photographer.

152
00:10:02,530 --> 00:10:04,120
Could you get a shot of us?

153
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:05,720
Sure thing.

154
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:08,500
<i>Sayaka's friends from high school.</i>

155
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:11,930
<i>Airi, and Chie.</i>

156
00:10:11,930 --> 00:10:14,390
You're saying one of them...

157
00:10:15,290 --> 00:10:17,620
poisoned Sayaka?

158
00:10:32,270 --> 00:10:34,760
[Chie: Can we talk?]

159
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:39,320
I apologize if this seemed so sudden.

160
00:10:40,710 --> 00:10:42,190
It's fine.

161
00:10:43,210 --> 00:10:49,200
I'm glad I asked Sayaka for your number.

162
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:51,410
I...

163
00:10:53,050 --> 00:10:56,040
I still can't believe what happened
at the wedding.

164
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:03,050
I haven't been able to sleep
because of the shock.

165
00:11:04,450 --> 00:11:07,600
I had no idea.

166
00:11:09,260 --> 00:11:15,490
I'm sorry for the trouble we've caused you.

167
00:11:15,490 --> 00:11:17,500
Don't apologize, Kazuomi.

168
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:20,050
It's not your fault.

169
00:11:20,650 --> 00:11:27,490
Sayaka is a dear friend. Of course I'd worry.

170
00:11:28,090 --> 00:11:29,510
Right.

171
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:34,630
Thank you.

172
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:40,340
Sayaka's a lucky girl.

173
00:11:41,410 --> 00:11:45,950
Where did she find a kind,
handsome man like you?

174
00:11:45,950 --> 00:11:49,050
You give me too much credit.

175
00:11:50,390 --> 00:11:52,630
I wish I had the same luck as she did.

176
00:11:54,390 --> 00:11:59,220
I broke up with my boyfriend just last month.

177
00:11:59,220 --> 00:12:00,440
What?

178
00:12:01,020 --> 00:12:03,890
He was cheating on me.

179
00:12:03,890 --> 00:12:06,720
I see...

180
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:09,820
[Sakuraba: Get to the point already.]

181
00:12:09,820 --> 00:12:12,230
Well... in any case...

182
00:12:13,130 --> 00:12:17,380
What was it you wanted to discuss with me?

183
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:19,650
Right.

184
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:24,750
Kazuomi.

185
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:29,250
Have you gone to get an exorcism?

186
00:12:30,220 --> 00:12:32,250
- Pardon?
- You should really go.

187
00:12:32,250 --> 00:12:37,210
I bet some evil spirit affected your wedding.

188
00:12:37,210 --> 00:12:38,720
You have to get rid of it!

189
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:39,790
I-Is that so...

190
00:12:39,790 --> 00:12:43,240
I know a spiritualist who can help.

191
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:45,420
They can see guardian spirits, too.

192
00:12:45,420 --> 00:12:48,630
Don't worry,
they won't sell you anything weird.

193
00:12:48,630 --> 00:12:51,430
I see.

194
00:12:56,410 --> 00:12:58,720
Don't worry, it'll wash out.

195
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:00,530
I'm so sorry.

196
00:13:00,530 --> 00:13:02,670
If you'll give me a moment.

197
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:10,050
Hey, what's the big idea?

198
00:13:10,810 --> 00:13:12,960
You were being sold on a scheme.

199
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:14,190
I was not.

200
00:13:14,190 --> 00:13:17,310
We're getting off track.

201
00:13:17,310 --> 00:13:20,930
You need to figure out if she's guilty.

202
00:13:20,930 --> 00:13:24,120
I can't just ask her if she poisoned Sayaka.

203
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:28,250
Then pinpoint a motive first.

204
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:32,400
Maybe she has something against Sayaka.

205
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:34,730
A motive...

206
00:13:38,210 --> 00:13:40,660
Sorry, did anything get stained?

207
00:13:40,660 --> 00:13:43,830
Nope. When should I schedule the exorcism?

208
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:47,980
Well, erm...

209
00:13:50,640 --> 00:13:52,030
Chie.

210
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:56,950
What do you think of Sayaka?

211
00:13:56,950 --> 00:14:01,170
Huh? Why ask?

212
00:14:01,170 --> 00:14:04,710
I, uh... got curious.

213
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:17,470
She's my best friend.

214
00:14:17,470 --> 00:14:19,840
Wasn't that obvious?

215
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:28,530
She's a bit timid, and faint-hearted.

216
00:14:28,530 --> 00:14:32,250
But that's part of why I like her.

217
00:14:33,010 --> 00:14:39,810
She could never do anything alone.
She needed someone at her side.

218
00:14:39,810 --> 00:14:41,640
Indeed.

219
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:46,240
I worried for her
when we graduated high school.

220
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:51,000
Especially with her juggling culinary school,
and her job at the ConCafe.

221
00:14:54,890 --> 00:14:56,940
ConCafe?
[T/N: a themed cafe, like a maid cafe]

222
00:14:57,580 --> 00:15:00,890
Sayaka worked at a ConCafe?

223
00:15:00,890 --> 00:15:04,190
Never mind. Please forget I said that.

224
00:15:04,190 --> 00:15:09,580
Like, one of those concept cafes?

225
00:15:13,420 --> 00:15:16,240
That's practically like working the nightlife.

226
00:15:27,020 --> 00:15:30,740
Please don't misunderstand.

227
00:15:30,740 --> 00:15:33,700
<i>Sayaka had her reasons.</i>

228
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:39,370
She had to pay her own tuition and rent,
without any support from her parents.

229
00:15:39,370 --> 00:15:42,040
She had to work a profitable job.

230
00:15:44,030 --> 00:15:50,610
If it's of any solace,
Sayaka never wore anything risqué.

231
00:15:50,610 --> 00:15:55,130
She avoided the nurse and animal cosplays.

232
00:15:55,900 --> 00:15:58,400
She always dressed as Little Red Riding Hood.

233
00:16:04,310 --> 00:16:07,600
[Unhappiest wishes to you, Red Riding Hood]

234
00:16:18,590 --> 00:16:22,560
What a downpour!
We're not even close to the station.

235
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:24,410
Far from it, really.

236
00:16:25,820 --> 00:16:31,020
You and Sayaka live in the area, right?

237
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:38,960
<i>Sayaka promised to invite me over
after the wedding.</i>

238
00:16:39,820 --> 00:16:42,370
Is that so.

239
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:46,190
I'm absolutely soaked.

240
00:16:54,350 --> 00:16:56,100
[Hayashida!]

241
00:16:57,920 --> 00:16:59,680
[Get a grip!]

242
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:02,670
[She's a suspect!]

243
00:17:02,670 --> 00:17:04,430
[Call ended]

244
00:17:08,670 --> 00:17:11,010
Seriously?

245
00:17:24,690 --> 00:17:27,980
Here, if you needed a change of clothes.
They're Sayaka's.

246
00:17:27,980 --> 00:17:30,240
No, I couldn't trouble you further.

247
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:33,020
I'll brew us some warm tea.

248
00:17:52,870 --> 00:17:54,700
You won't be changing?

249
00:17:54,700 --> 00:17:57,950
No, I feel bad about borrowing clothes.

250
00:17:57,950 --> 00:18:00,440
It's really no big deal.

251
00:18:09,910 --> 00:18:12,900
Kazuomi.

252
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:14,250
Yes?

253
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:24,410
Your hands.

254
00:18:25,870 --> 00:18:28,080
Could I see them?

255
00:18:28,830 --> 00:18:30,150
My hands?

256
00:18:30,930 --> 00:18:34,930
I can read palms.

257
00:18:34,930 --> 00:18:36,920
It's a specialty of mine.

258
00:18:45,370 --> 00:18:50,670
I knew it. You do have a heart of gold.

259
00:18:52,780 --> 00:18:55,420
You also have a strong sense of justice.

260
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:03,870
You take action for the sake of others.

261
00:19:08,460 --> 00:19:11,980
I think that's wonderful.

262
00:19:48,850 --> 00:19:50,940
There you go.

263
00:19:53,040 --> 00:19:55,090
Why did you hang up?

264
00:19:55,090 --> 00:19:59,830
You suddenly bombarded me with texts.

265
00:20:01,930 --> 00:20:04,200
I'm freezing...

266
00:20:10,590 --> 00:20:11,980
Is everything alright?

267
00:20:11,980 --> 00:20:14,000
Yes, fine.

268
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,880
<i>She was getting suspicious.</i>

269
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:17,870
So you brought her here.

270
00:20:17,870 --> 00:20:22,230
I'm ashamed I doubted her for even a second.

271
00:20:23,260 --> 00:20:25,680
I think that's wonderful.

272
00:20:27,830 --> 00:20:29,290
Chie.

273
00:20:30,450 --> 00:20:31,990
Yes?

274
00:20:35,860 --> 00:20:37,640
Thank you.

275
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:44,010
Sayaka has such wonderful friends.

276
00:20:52,700 --> 00:20:54,670
Kazuomi.

277
00:20:57,540 --> 00:21:02,690
Thank you for marrying Sayaka.

278
00:21:02,690 --> 00:21:03,960
Huh?

279
00:21:04,560 --> 00:21:08,670
Sayaka's my best friend.

280
00:21:08,670 --> 00:21:13,830
Let me know if you ever need my help, okay?

281
00:21:13,830 --> 00:21:18,140
I would do anything for Sayaka.

282
00:21:18,930 --> 00:21:22,870
Chie wasn't suspicious after all.

283
00:21:22,870 --> 00:21:26,820
Hayashida. You're absolutely useless.

284
00:21:26,820 --> 00:21:28,900
What? Rude.

285
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:32,300
We're looking for the individual
who poisoned your wife.

286
00:21:32,300 --> 00:21:34,370
And she's one of our suspects.

287
00:21:34,370 --> 00:21:38,690
You'd get it if you spoke to her, Sakuraba.

288
00:21:38,690 --> 00:21:44,880
She thanked me for marrying Sayaka.
Only a true friend would say that.

289
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:49,630
That's not a blessing people give,
friend or otherwise.

290
00:21:49,630 --> 00:21:54,570
If anything, it seems rather condescending.

291
00:21:54,570 --> 00:21:59,400
That was no slip of the tongue.

292
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:01,980
And neither was her mentioning the ConCafe.

293
00:22:03,080 --> 00:22:07,660
But you knew about the job, didn't you?

294
00:22:07,660 --> 00:22:09,810
Of course not.

295
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:19,200
This isn't getting anywhere.

296
00:22:20,660 --> 00:22:23,220
Let's switch topics.

297
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:29,920
The other day,

298
00:22:30,910 --> 00:22:38,420
you mentioned Sayaka was harassed
on food review sites.

299
00:22:38,420 --> 00:22:39,840
Right.

300
00:22:41,250 --> 00:22:43,730
After looking into it a bit further,

301
00:22:43,730 --> 00:22:48,410
those reviews led me to a certain individual.

302
00:22:55,510 --> 00:22:56,790
[Me and the bestie, Sayaka]

303
00:22:56,790 --> 00:23:03,300
She's the most suspicious one yet.

304
00:23:03,300 --> 00:23:05,050
Airi?

305
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:08,650
[Me and the bestie, Sayaka]
